Background|access-date = 2015-12-19|publisher = Kenya Re}} == Overview == Kenya Re is the oldest reinsurer in [[East Africa|Eastern]] and [[Central Africa]] and serves over 265 insurances companies in 62 countries across [[Africa]], the [[Middle East]] and [[Asia]] with over 50 percent of its revenue being generated from foreign markets.{{Cite web|url = http://www.businessdailyafrica.com/Kenya-Re-profit-20pc-up-as-it-eyes-oil/-/539552/2829858/-/jod9n3z/-/index.html|title = Kenya Re profit 20pc up as it eyes oil|date = August 12, 2015|access-date = December 19, 2015|website = [[Business Daily Africa]]|publisher = [[Nation Media Group]]}} The firm provides reinsurance products to both [[Life insurance|life]] and [[general insurance]].{{Cite web|url = http://in.reuters.com/finance/stocks/companyProfile?symbol=KNRE.NR|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151222124012/http://in.reuters.com/finance/stocks/companyProfile?symbol=KNRE.NR|url-status = dead|archive-date = 2015-12-22|title = Kenya Reinsurance Corp Ltd (KNRE.NR)|access-date = 2015-12-20|website = [[Reuters]]|publisher = [[Thomson Reuters]]}} Kenya Re is listed on the [[Nairobi Securities Exchange]]. == History == Kenya Reinsurance Corporation was established through an [[Parliament of Kenya|Act of Parliament]] in December 1970. The firm commenced reinsurance business in January 1971. Kenya Re launched its IPO in 2007 leading to the government cutting its stake in the reinsurer.{{Cite web|url = https://brandkemistry.wordpress.com/2007/08/20/kenya-re-share-allocation-ends-in-favour-of-insurers/|title = Kenya Re share allocation ends in favour of insurers|date = August 20, 2007|access-date = December 20, 2015}} == Ownership == The shares of the [[stock]] of Kenya Reinsurance Corporation are traded on the Nairobi Securities Exchange, under the symbol: '''KNRE'''.{{Cite web|url = https://www.nse.co.ke/listed-companies/list.html|title = Listed Companies|access-date = 2015-12-20|publisher = NSE|archive-date = 28 September 2020|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20200928092308/https://www.nse.co.ke/listed-companies/list.html|url-status = dead}} {{As of|2014|December|31}}, the shareholding in the group's stock was as depicted in the table below:{{Cite book|title = Kenya Reinsurance Corporation - 2014 Annual Report|year = 2014|location = Nairobi|url = https://www.kenyare.co.ke/index.php/example-pages/annual-report/105-kenyare-annual-accounts-for-fy-2015/file}} {| class="wikitable sortable" style="margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto" |+ Kenya Reinsurance Corporation''' Stock Ownership''' ! contentMetadata.text: Kenya Reinsurance Corporation Limited commonly referred to as Kenya Re is a reinsurance company based in Nairobi, Kenya. Kenya Re is the oldest reinsurer in Eastern and Central Africa and serves over 265 insurances companies in 62 countries across Africa, the Middle East and Asia with over 50 percent of its revenue being generated from foreign markets. The firm provides reinsurance products to both life and general insurance. Kenya Re is listed on the Nairobi Securities Exchange. Kenya Reinsurance Corporation was established through an Act of Parliament in December 1970. The firm commenced reinsurance business in January 1971. Kenya Re launched its IPO in 2007 leading to the government cutting its stake in the reinsurer. The shares of the stock of Kenya Reinsurance Corporation are traded on the Nairobi Securities Exchange, under the symbol: KNRE. As of 31 December 2014[update], the shareholding in the group's stock was as depicted in the table below: Kenya Re is governed by an eleven-person Board of Directors with Jennifer Karina serving as the chairperson of the group and Jadiah Mwarania as the managing director.
